                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Fear kiting at lvl 22 seems to be a very mana draining strategy.  I've played an untwinked necro on FV and a twinked necro now, and in both cases I was able to tank mobs up to at least lvl 30.  <br /><br />Granted, I didn't necessarily tank the whole fight, but I took some hits.  This is good because it helps build up your defense skills, and it helps to balance the three bars that are important to you:<br /><br />* Your Mana bar<br />* Your Health bar<br />* Pet Health bar<br /><br />At the lower lvls, I personally try to never have any one of them completely full, but rather try to balance them out so I'm getting good use of my pet as well as my health and mana.  <br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
