                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Aye i generally still use a mixture even at level 34. Quite often ill let my pet tank if the mob doesnt hit to hard while healing it with shadow compact. If its a hard hitter then I generally fear kite or sometimes ill DS myself and melee a bit to raise defence skills. Can also aggro kite by casting a few dots on em and maybe  a lifetap, turn pet taunt off, then have the mob run around after you while your pet beats on it, I use this one mostly when I have sow as I can run away and med then run again.<br /><br />For hunting spots, I soloed the shik'nar in PC till 23, then grouped at bandits till 25, then I headed to Unrest to play around (found out you really need a group to do well here), Marus Seru might be the best spot to solo at 25 (if you can afford it buy your pet a set of mage focus items - Muzzle of Mardu, Fists of Xziblat sp, girdle of the magi'kot helps a lot. I also found that on my server at least nightrage staffs were going for 10pp so I bought them for my pet which more than doubled his dmg). I moved to Dawnshroud Peaks at level 31 and soloed lightcrawlers/zelniaks to level 33, then mushrooms to where im at now.<br /><br />Hope that helps some :)</span id="msg"></font></td>
