                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> First the best place for xp at your level is PC.  At 22, all the bandits should be blue and you should be able to fear kite them quite easily.  Just make sure you get solo pulls.  Best way to do this is to xp there while a group is pulling.  This should leave you with singles that you can fear kite fairly easily.  If there isn’t a group pulling and singles are hard to come buy, just do fiends till you hit level 24.<br /><br />At level 24-29 or 24-33 you can move over to Echo Caverns and do Needlits very easily using Banshee Aura.  The camp I believe has 6 needlits with the one in the back/middle being the place holder for the Needlit Queen.  All pulls except the place holder and the one to it’s right are solo pulls.  For the other two you just need to use your new spell Screaming Terror on um.  If resisted, FD immediately.  Enter needlit cavern invis and move to the corner on the left side of the entrance.  Make your pet and buff up and put on Banshee Aura (your damage shield).  Pull with Darkness snare and sick pet on needlit just before it gets to you.  Now walk into it’s agro radius and let it hit you while pet is still attacking it.  When your life total gets to about 70% back off and let pet tank while you cast your DD lifetap on it, then retank.  Do this one or two more times and it will be dead.<br /><br />Or if you want you can fear kite them fairly easily once the room is cleared.  Again pull with Darkness, sick pet, fear it, then land a few dots and let it run off.  You won’t be able to get any loot this way though as they will run down into the hall where those plants that root/DD you are and it will inevitably happen that you will step on one and have it agro you.  At that point you either have to log or zone to get rid of it’s agro.  So if you don’t need the $$ don’t bother looting the corpse.<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
